To be direct and honest, if I was on Twitter to sell a subscription to a service or seeking to build my "franchise" as an 'influencer,' etc. -- I could see accepting the abusive responses. But I am not seeking those ends, Rev. I couldn't care less about that stuff.

I, too, have no fear of critics. As u know I believe in respectful debate. I block haters that are disrespectful and not those that simply disagree with me. This is my personal thread, just like everyone else, I should be allowed to express my non market views.
So why exactly do you follow me? You are blocked, as I really dont care.

Feel free to unfollow me Ryan. If that is your view you might consider it. I write this respectfully. But I am not sure why I shouldnt be entitled to express my political views/observations as everyone else does. This is my personal thread. Be well.
I know, goes with the terrain. The question is why I even bother to give out free ideas/views. Its a good question that I often ask myself Robert.

To my trolls on Twitter (who seem to have multiplied lately) - at least, win/lose/draw, I put my trades/investments out. I dont sweep the losers under the rug and I dont herald only wins -as many in fin media do. I am done for the week having blocked a record # of twitter beasts

I am not sure why haters even bother to follow me - I guess it speaks volumes about them. My analysis and deeper dives, as always, is on @realmoney Enjoy the week, the weekend and I should be returning on Monday.
